            "body":"In addition to the university – and the city – being built on <a class='network-link' href='#/city/intro#burial'>Ho Chunk land</a>, the Land-Grant College Act (or Morrill Act), passed by Congress in 1862, gave universities land that had been expropriated from indigenous communities to States to help finance the establishment of colleges."
